00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:01.750
- [Instructor] One of the core ideas

00:00:01.750 --> 00:00:04.480
of Thomas Piketty's book
is if the return on capital

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:06.870
is greater than the growth in economy,

00:00:06.870 --> 00:00:09.410
then that could drive inequality.

00:00:09.410 --> 00:00:12.183
That could drive inequality.

00:00:13.460 --> 00:00:14.410
Inequality.

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:17.490
And inequality is a natural
byproduct of a market

00:00:17.490 --> 00:00:19.987
capitalist economy and
one could argue that,

00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:23.462
"Hey, look, some inequality
is going to happen

00:00:23.462 --> 00:00:25.047
"as you grow your economy
and you let people

00:00:25.047 --> 00:00:27.217
"be entrepreneurial, and
some people get lucky,

00:00:27.217 --> 00:00:29.247
"some people less lucky,
some people work harder,

00:00:29.247 --> 00:00:31.687
"some people work less
hard, some people are able

00:00:31.687 --> 00:00:33.850
"to allocate capital
well, some people aren't."

00:00:33.850 --> 00:00:36.550
So it all comes into
it, but in extreme forms

00:00:36.550 --> 00:00:37.630
maybe this is bad.

00:00:37.630 --> 00:00:40.660
And in particular, maybe
this is bad for democracy.

00:00:40.660 --> 00:00:44.170
So bad for democracy right over here.

00:00:44.170 --> 00:00:47.300
Maybe too much power starts
to accrue in some ways.

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:48.930
And maybe that and in the worst case

00:00:48.930 --> 00:00:52.370
because that kind of starts
to drive in on itself.

00:00:52.370 --> 00:00:54.390
It actually might even
hurt economic growth

00:00:54.390 --> 00:00:57.120
if you don't have enough
consumers or people

00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:59.490
with enough purchasing
power, discretionary income.

00:00:59.490 --> 00:01:01.420
Or whatever else.

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:03.540
But what I really wanna focus on here

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:06.880
is not so much whether these causalities

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:09.210
are actually there or how much
we should worry about them.

00:01:09.210 --> 00:01:11.770
Once again, my point
isn't to give an opinion

00:01:11.770 --> 00:01:15.410
